					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rhettsarlin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(300030); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=300030&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182726" alt="RhettSarlin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=300030)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rhettsarlin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(300030); return false;" >RhettSarlin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1346540737 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Sep 2012 23:05</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1553974">
									

<p>i havent even read them yet, all i've done so far is open them. as soon as i saw how long they were, and the sort of style you were writing in, i upvoted every page :P now to hope that that is not rescinded by the contents. <em>don't disappoint me</em></p>
<p>how long did this take you?</p>
<p>*edit*</p>
<p>disappointment: non-existent. this was absolutely amazing. looks to be 44,000 - 45,000 words all told&#8230;.so about 127 pages for your average paperback. double that and you've got a bonafide novel on your hands. you have an in-depth, coherent, and even devious plot, plenty of intrigue, interesting characters, and dramatic tension that kept me wanting more. you properly used a wide variety of SCP materials, to the point that i found myself going back to review the entries in question to see just how well you HAD used them.</p>
<p>the only thing i worry about is that it's so long that you won't get many who finish the entire thing. if that's the case, don't get discouraged! you are a pretty awesome writer here.</p>

							</div>

								
