					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/alamac" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1421060); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1421060&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182726" alt="Alamac" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1421060)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/alamac" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1421060); return false;" >Alamac</a></span> <span class="odate time_1346901762 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Sep 2012 03:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1557368">
									

<p>This is probably one of the best tales I have ever read on this site, at the very least I think it would take gold for the longest. It created an in-depth atmosphere, gave a close look at an intriguing GOI, as well as having a genuine air of darkness about it. Not only did you make the characters have depth, you also managed to make the dialog seem natural (even with the action-movie-like part at the end), something a lot of articles and tales do not pull off as masterfully as this did. When I finally start writing stuff, I will be happy having written something half as good as this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
